Date: 0/0/1988
Source: Dictionary of Kiwi Slang, A
Author: McGILL
Vol / Page: 102
Edition:
Quote: SHREWD HEAD/SHREWDIE <i>shrewd head/shrewdie </i> a shrewd person, that latter applying also to a shrewd trick, in phr. <i>pull a shrewdie </i>; eg `If you're going to play poker with him be on your guard, for sure he'll pull a shrewdie.' NZA.
